title: Narrative

Vertical interactive `<<tabs>>` (via `pitch-class="tc-vertical"`) compared to the static-tabs auto-delegated rendering. Static rendering ignores the vertical orientation since each tab becomes its own block-level card.

+
title: Output

;Interactive vertical tabs

<$let pitch-class="tc-vertical">
<$transclude $tiddler="StaticTabs" $mode="block"/>
</$let>

-----

;Static-render mode (tv-config-static="yes" auto-delegates; class="tc-vertical" passes through but has no effect on stacked cards)

<$let tv-config-static="yes" pitch-class="tc-vertical">
<$transclude $tiddler="StaticTabs" $mode="block"/>
</$let>
